{
  "version": "2026-07-seed-v6-endpoint-privilege-mgmt",
  "note": "Default Bundle -> outcome coverage library, keyed by Bundle key (see seeds/bundles.json) and outcomes.json keys. Seeded (ratified) into engagement-scoped CoverageMapEntry rows (bundle_id set) on engagement creation. A first-pass authored default from standard Microsoft SKU inclusions — the SA refines per engagement (and, later, the global library) in the GUI. Security outcomes are split: Endpoint = EPP (anti-malware/AV) vs EDR (behavioral detection); Email = Hygiene (EOP) vs Advanced Threat Protection (Defender for Office 365). Identity is split three ways: SSO/IdP (cloud directory + single sign-on, on any Entra/Azure AD tenant — so every M365/O365 suite has it) vs MFA & Conditional Access (Entra P1: multi-factor + dynamic/adaptive access policies — NOT basic security-defaults, so O365 and Business Basic/Standard lack it) vs Governance (Entra P2: PIM/Identity Protection/access reviews). Collaboration is now Team Chat & Meetings (the Teams-vs-Slack/Zoom hub) — desktop apps and cloud storage are their own outcomes.",
